title: Cardinal freshmen finish tournament play
text:
Cardinal freshmen finish tournament play Published: Monday, Oct. 19, 2015 11:34 a.m. CDT • Updated: Monday, Oct. 19, 2015 11:35 a.m. CDT By Jocelyn Sheets Newton Daily News 
DES MOINES — Playing in their final tournament of the season, Newton High’s freshmen split two pool matches to reach the consolation bracket of Saturday’s Des Moines Lincoln freshman volleyball tournament. 
Newton lost the first set against Des Moines North 21-11 and posted a 21-13 win in the second set. Tegan Simmons had an 11-point serving run for the Cardinals. She had five aces in the match and went 12-of-15 serving. 
Brittney McConnell put down two kills and Simmons had one kill. Carolyn-Kaye Kimmel had one ace serve and one kill. Sierra Anderson had an ace serve and Desirae Shelton was credited with a dig. 
It was the same pattern against Des Moines Lincoln — losing the first set 21-9 and winning the second set 21-19. Simmons served up three aces and had one kill. McConnell downed two kills, had an ace serve and one dig. Anderson had four ace serves and Shelton had one kill. 
The Cardinals lost 21-11, 21-13 to Valley in pool play and 21-3, 21-12 to Southeast Polk. In those two matches, Simmons had three ace serves and Anderson had one ace serve. At the net, McConnell and Kimmel each had two kills while Kyleigh Stevenson had one kill. 
In the consolation bracket, Ottumwa beat Newton, 25-13, 25-6. McConnell had two kills and an ace serve. Simmons and Shelton each downed a kill. 
“We made some adjustments with the lineup and the girls adjusted accordingly,” Newton freshman coach Michaela Wood said. “We will have Monday to freshen up and then finish the season at Norwalk on Tuesday.”
